The Federal Capital Territory Alumni association of the College of Education, Zuba, yesterday donated some waste bins to the college for proper disposal of waste in the college. President of the association, Comrade Unimna Felix Unimna while handing over the items along with other executive members of the group, said the gesture was to show their appreciation to the college for providing them with sound education and making them proud in their respective places of work. Provost of the College, Dr. Gambo Hamza, while inspecting the 20 waste bins thanked the alumni and assured that the items would enhance the sanitation of the college. The college registrar, Dr. Grace N. Tyoden said the gesture would motivate other students to also give back to their alma mater.